Lasso Ridge et lambda

kevin caye

24 janvier 2017

library(tidyverse)
library(Article3Package)
cl <- parallel::makeCluster(4)
doParallel::registerDoParallel(cl)

normal dataset

K = 6
L = 1000
n = 100
cs <- list()
cs[[3]] <- 0.9
# sample data
s <- NormalSampler(n = n,
                   L = L,
                   K = K,
                   prop.outlier = 0.2, 
                   sigma = 0.2,
                   c = NULL,
                   cs = cs)
LassoRidgeEtLambda(s, method.K = 4,
                   exp.rep = 1,
                   ridge.lambda.low = 1e-10,
                   ridge.lambda.medium = 1e0,
                   ridge.lambda.high = 1e10,
                   sparse.prop = 0.1, 
                   gif = TRUE)
Hypothesis testing comparison

                       n = n,
                       L = L,
                       K = K,
                       prop.outlier = 0.10,
                       rho = NULL,
                       cs = cs,
                       round = FALSE)
LassoRidgeEtLambda(s, method.K = 3,
                   exp.rep = 3,
                   ridge.lambda.low = 1e-5,
                   ridge.lambda.medium = 1e4,
                   ridge.lambda.high = 1e15,

                   gif = TRUE)
